[15:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'know. At least I\'m about 75% sure I don\'t know, and at least 35% sure that that joke landed. Which does lead us to the next section, and one that I think is going to be a major part of AI video'

[16:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'creation, and one that you will be hearing a lot more of in the upcoming months. It basically boils down to MCPs, which if you\'re not familiar with, is a model context protocol. This is a thing that allows an LLM to talk to external'

[16:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tools like Photoshop, Canva, or a host of others. And now we are starting to see it on AI video generation platforms as well. Now, I am going to say off the bat, this is a bit of a preview for a'

[16:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'larger video that I will be doing on the topic, because well, I mean, things get things get a little crazy. So, just kind of consider this a bit of a primer. We\'ll be taking a look at this on two spots, Flora and Martini, both of which'

[16:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have MCP connectors, but that list is growing every day. Actually, Runway just announced theirs. We\'re actually going to kick this off over on Flora, mostly because I actually haven\'t made the MCP connection on Flora, so I think this'

[16:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'will be a good walk-through. On this side, of course, I have Claude Code set up, and then on this side, this is, you know, the Flora website. Obviously, you can connect the MCP to Claude Code, Cursor, VS Code, Hermes,'

[17:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Open Claw, etc., etc. So, I mean, we\'re going to fire it off in Claude. And now, what\'s funny is that when I say install, I really just mean, uh, you know, just grabbing this line and, uh, copy-pasting it into into'

[17:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Claude. Uh, and then we\'re going to fire this off. From there, I mean, it\'s actually, I mean, it\'s pretty stupidly simple. I just asked Claude, you know, do you have the floor MCP working? It was like, yep, connected. Uh, and then it was like, oh, well, you\'re not authorized yet. You want me to You want'

[17:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'me to fire off an authorization link? Gave me a URL. I I clicked connect, basically connecting the accounts. It was like, all right, we\'re good. Uh, and then from there, it was like, go into this Claude test folder. And from there, I mean, we\'re basically off and running.'

