AUDIO: 'out of him. So, I thought that was actually kind of funny. The other interesting thing with MCPs as well, actually I got to admit Claude came up with this one. Uh, you know when we\'re doing our like nano banana 4 by 4s, uh, in 2 1, this is technique that I often'

[20:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'use. Essentially, you\'re buying more, uh, you know, generation out of like one generation. Uh, well, I Claude came up with the idea of like, hey, I have the Adobe MCP loaded up into here. I can just take that this, you know, four up'

[20:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and then I can, uh, bring it over to, uh, I can do the slices myself. I was like, yeah, why why don\'t you do that? Cuz that part that part\'s pain. Now, I do have to say, is it fast? I mean, not particularly. I mean, it obviously gets'

[20:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'slowed down by things like nano banana generations and, uh, C dance generations, which can be notoriously slow. Um, but, you know, the way that I end up using it is essentially not so much as a co-pilot, but like, you know, an extra set of hands. So, I\'ll have it'

[20:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'working on one section while I\'m working on another. And because it essentially has the full context of everything that we\'re working on, I mean, it does a pretty good job, uh, more or less left to its own devices. You know,'

